  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life-saving food assistance for IDPs, returnees and host communities in crisis affected locations.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project consists of the provision of in-kind assistance, in which the food security needs of beneficiaries will be addressed in out-of-camp settings. The planned intervention targets the highly vulnerable host communities, returnees and IDP&#x2019;s in villages and spontaneous settlements north of Mosul, covering Hamdaniya and Tilkaif districts. The project will be implemented by Dorcas Aid International (DORCAS). DORCAS has been delivering food assistance for the past 5 months as response to the Mosul emergency, resulting in extensive experience in the areas of intervention. 

Furthermore, and in accordance to the IHPF 2017 first standard allocation paper, which establishes food support as one the main needs of the population affected by the military operation to retake Mosul, DORCAS aims to serve 60,462 direct beneficiaries out of the 3.2 million individuals that are currently food insecure and forced to rely on severe and often irreversible coping mechanisms. This will be done through the acquisition and distribution of 10,077 dry food parcels. The composition of the food parcels follows the recommendation of the World Food Program (WFP) and the Food Security Cluster and contains sufficient food for a household of six individuals for a period of twenty days. The distribution of the food parcels will be conducted in coordination with the Food Security Cluster. Given the fact that the PDS system is unable to support the population with food assistance in the areas of intervention, the distribution of in-kind food assistance is highly needed. 

This project is meant to be a continuation of the food security program implemented by DORCAS over the past five months in order to alleviate the suffering of the population affected by the ongoing violence and unrest in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
